### Example 02: Route Parameters
### Server: http://localhost:3000

### Path Parameter - Get User by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1

### Path Parameter - Get User by ID (not found)
GET http://localhost:3000/users/999

### Update User - Path + Body params
PUT http://localhost:3000/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Smith",
  "email": "alice.smith@example.com"
}

### Delete User
DELETE http://localhost:3000/users/2

### Query Parameters - All products
GET http://localhost:3000/products

### Query Parameters - Filter by category
GET http://localhost:3000/products?category=electronics

### Query Parameters - Filter by price range
GET http://localhost:3000/products?min_price=100&max_price=500

### Query Parameters - Combined filters
GET http://localhost:3000/products?category=furniture&max_price=250

### Query Parameters - With limit
GET http://localhost:3000/products?category=electronics&limit=1

### Combined - Path + Query
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1/products

### Combined - User's electronics
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1/products?category=electronics

### Combined - User's products over $100
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1/products?min_price=100
